                                    <version>Lustre 2.9.0</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="163317" author="simmonsja" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2016 21:48:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I updated the server side up to the latest master since it was over a month old and when I attempted to reproduce this problem it went away. So it looks like a version mismatch in version of pre-2.9 caused this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="163243" author="laisiyao" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2016 14:07:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The backtrace shows it&apos;s a soft lockup in mdt_lock_root_xattr()-&amp;gt;mdt_remote_object_lock(), which is introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7660&quot; title=&quot;FS default striping settings only honored on MDT 0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7660&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7660&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, however this root XATTR lock is not held (i.e., decref-ed right after taken), I don&apos;t see why it will cause soft lockup. Could you get backtraces of the MDS where the soft lockup occurs? and are all MDT locked up?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW, do you think it&apos;s happens with Power8 clients only?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="163215" author="jgmitter" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2016 05:22:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Lai,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please help to investigate this issue?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
Joe&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
